---
// Privacy Policy — finalized 2026-06-07 (best-effort, NOT lawyer-reviewed; the
// owner opted out of counsel). Substance: the APP is local-first (reads ~/.claude
// on-device, no telemetry) with a fixed, audited outbound set — GitHub updates,
// a no-data license-revocation download, and YouTube when Claude Radio is started
// (verified against ../conan this session). The WEBSITE collects a signup email
// (Vercel/Upstash KV + Resend) and, on purchase, the buyer email tied to the
// license (Polar = Merchant of Record); GA4 analytics disclosed. No more
// DRAFT/.todo placeholders.
//
// KNOWN PRODUCT-SIDE GAPS (in ../conan, not fixable here — policy makes promises
// the product should honor): (1) the license JWT embeds the buyer email base64-
// readable; (2) no automated deletion path, so §7 erasure requests must be
// fulfilled MANUALLY (purge license:<sub> KV + scrub Vercel logs). (3) GA4 loads
// with NO consent banner — a real EU/UK ePrivacy risk the policy text alone
// doesn't cure. Address these before/right after launch.
import LegalLayout from "../layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
---

<LegalLayout
  active="privacy"
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="What Conan and conan.sh collect — and what they deliberately don't."
  updated="June 7, 2026"
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how WhatMatters LLC ("WhatMatters", "we", "us") handles
    information in connection with the Conan application and the conan.sh
    website. The short version: the app is built to keep your work on your
    machine, and the website collects only the minimum needed to send Conan
    updates and sell Premium.
  </p>

  <section id="overview">
    <h2>1. Overview</h2>
    <p>
      There are two surfaces to distinguish. The <strong>Conan app</strong> runs
      entirely on your Mac and sends us no telemetry. The <strong>conan.sh
      website</strong> collects limited data when you sign up for updates or
      purchase Premium. This policy covers both.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="collect">
    <h2>2. Data we collect (website)</h2>
    <h3>News &amp; updates signup</h3>
    <p>
      If you sign up for Conan news and updates, we collect the <strong>email
      address</strong> you submit, so we can send you occasional updates — new
      features, releases, and Windows/Linux availability. This is stored in our
      key-value store (Vercel/Upstash KV) and forwarded to our team inbox via
      <strong>Resend</strong>. You can unsubscribe at any time.
    </p>
    <h3>Purchases</h3>
    <p>
      When you buy Premium, payment is processed by <strong>Polar.sh</strong> as
      Merchant of Record. Polar collects the information needed to complete the
      sale (e.g. billing details) and we <strong>do not store your full
      payment-card details</strong>. When your order completes, we do receive and
      <strong>store your email address</strong> together with your order id and
      license record — we use it to deliver your license, recognize your purchase,
      and provide support. Your email is also embedded in your signed license token
      so the app can confirm the license is yours. Because of this, please keep
      your license private and do not post it publicly. You can ask us to delete
      your stored purchase email at any time (see <a href="#rights">Your rights</a>).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="app">
    <h2>3. The app: local-only</h2>
    <p>
      Conan reads Claude Code's local session data in <strong>~/.claude</strong>
      to visualize your activity. This processing happens on your device. Conan
      does not transmit your code, prompts, or session contents to us or any
      third party, and the app sends <strong>no analytics or telemetry</strong>.
    </p>
    <p>
      The app makes only a small, fixed set of outbound connections, and none of
      them send your personal data to us:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Software updates</strong> — Conan checks GitHub for new signed
        releases so it can keep itself up to date.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>License revocation check</strong> — on launch, Conan downloads a
        public revocation list to confirm a Premium license has not been revoked.
        This is a download only: it transmits no personal data and does not send
        your license. License validity itself is verified entirely on your device.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Claude Radio</strong> — if you start the built-in radio, audio
        streams directly from YouTube. As with any embedded YouTube player,
        Google / YouTube receives your IP address and may set its own cookies
        under its own privacy policy. The radio is off until you start it.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Choosing "Buy Premium" or opening a documentation link launches your normal
      web browser, outside the app.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="use">
    <h2>4. How we use data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>to send you occasional Conan news and updates if you signed up (you can unsubscribe anytime);</li>
      <li>to fulfill and support your Premium purchase;</li>
      <li>to operate, secure, and improve the website.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We use signup emails <strong>only</strong> to send Conan product news; we
      never sell them or use them for unrelated marketing. We do not sell your
      personal information.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="processors">
    <h2>5. Sharing & processors</h2>
    <p>We share data only with service providers that help us run the Service:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Polar.sh</strong> — payments / Merchant of Record;</li>
      <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — hosting and the KV store that holds signup emails;</li>
      <li><strong>Resend</strong> — to deliver our news/update emails and signup notifications;</li>
      <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — aggregate, cookie-based website analytics (see §8).</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Each of these providers processes data under its own privacy terms, and we
      do not share your data with any other third parties for their own purposes.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="retention">
    <h2>6. Data retention</h2>
    <p>
      We keep signup emails for as long as you wish to receive Conan updates, or
      until you unsubscribe or ask us to remove you. Purchase records (including
      the email tied to your license) are retained as required for tax and
      accounting purposes.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="rights">
    <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on where you live (e.g. under GDPR or CCPA), you may have rights
      to access, correct, delete, or port your personal data, and to object to
      certain processing. To exercise these, email <a
        href="mailto:hello@conan.sh">hello@conan.sh</a
      > and we will respond within a reasonable time and as required by applicable
      law. We will not discriminate against you for exercising these rights.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="cookies">
    <h2>8. Cookies & analytics</h2>
    <p>
      The conan.sh website uses <strong>Google Analytics (GA4)</strong> to
      understand aggregate, anonymized traffic — for example, which pages are
      visited and roughly where visitors arrive from. Google Analytics sets
      cookies in your browser for this purpose. We use this only to improve the
      website; we do not use it to build advertising profiles or sell your data.
      You can opt out with Google's
      <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout">browser opt-out add-on</a>
      or by blocking cookies in your browser. The <strong>Conan app itself
      contains no analytics or telemetry</strong> (see §3).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="children">
    <h2>9. Children's privacy</h2>
    <p>
      The Service is not directed to anyone under 18, and we do not knowingly
      collect personal information from children. If you believe a minor has
      provided us personal information, contact us and we will delete it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="intl">
    <h2>10. International users</h2>
    <p>
      Our service providers are based primarily in the United States, so if you
      access the Service from elsewhere, your information may be processed in the
      United States and other countries with different data-protection laws. Where
      personal data is transferred internationally, we rely on appropriate
      safeguards — such as our providers' standard contractual clauses — where
      required by law.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="changes">
    <h2>11. Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy; the "Last updated" date above will reflect any
      changes, and we will notify you of material changes as required.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="contact">
    <h2>12. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about your privacy? Email <a href="mailto:hello@conan.sh"
        >hello@conan.sh</a
      >.
    </p>
  </section>
</LegalLayout>
